short_summary: Must translate from English to French with variable document length, and pass a written exam as part of the bid process. Must provide documentation, specify maximum mail file size and orientation, making it inclusive.
description: English to French translation services are required by the Canadian Institutes of Health Research (CIHR). The translation of documents from English to French will be needed as and when required. Up to 8 contracts may be awarded. Documents will vary from approximately 50 to 50 000 words, and therefore applicants should be aware that they may need to translate short or long documents. Furthermore, as part of the bid process, all shortlisted bidders will be required to participate in a written exam. The exam will test the bidding firm's ability to meet the contract requirements, specifically it will simulate a translation request and check the firm's ability to translate the document correctly and meet the required deadline. The format of the exam and the translation will be announced separately. The contract start date is April 1, 2023, and the end date is March 31, 2024. The contract may be extended by up to two additional one-year periods under the same conditions.",
